<!-- post # 16 --><font color="#FF0000">SCARS</font><br><tt>Tue Nov 12  9:44:51 US/Eastern 1996</tt><p>Cloud of Red <br>By Jack Wright <br>1st Cavalry Division, 1966-67<br><br>Deaf John Wise came traveling down the road<br>Looking for old friends to help him with his load<br>Caught up in a war over in Vietnam<br>Praying for forgiveness <br>He's a full grown man<br><br>Born in the hills of the old Virginia south<br>Where he learned to love his country <br>And never open his mouth<br>Don't get me wrong he loved his neighbors and kin<br>But in these changing times its hard to tell<br>A devil from a friend<br><br>When Johnny reached the shore <br>It was early in the Spring<br>There were 100s just like him<br>They all began to scream<br>Save our souls from death<br>Lord, save our souls from fear<br>We'll gladly serve our country <br>and be back home in a year<br><br>The day that he remembers most <br>Was the 1st day of July<br>He was guarding prisoners <br>And I cannot tell you why<br>An old, old man he began to run<br>He was looking for his freedom<br>Johnny got his gun<br><br>The old man hit the river<br>It was such a sight to see<br>The other prisoners cheered him on<br>They wanted him to be free <br>Johnny took his aim <br>And he saw that old gray head<br>When he squeezed the trigger<br>He saw a Cloud of Red<br><br>Right there in front of him <br>Before his very eyes<br>He saw his own grandfather <br>And heard hid mournful cry<br>That was the last thing old deaf Johnny heard<br>And all of his old friends say<br>He never speaks a word<br><br>Deaf John Wise is traveling down your road<br>Looking for old friends to help him with his load<br>Caught up in a war over in Vietnam<br>Praying for forgiveness, He's a full grown man<br><br>copyright Jack Wright, Moonbow Music, BMI<br><p><code>-- wrighte@oak.cats.ohiou.edu  (jack wright) </code><p>